Italy's overall balance of payments showed a919 billion lire surplus in September against a deficit of1,026 billion in August, provisional Bank of Italy figuresshowed.    The September surplus compared with a shortfall of 1,697billion lire in September 1986. For the first nine months of1987, the overall balance of payments showed a deficit of 1,921billion lire against a 1,725 billion deficit in the same 1986period.    The central bank said Italy's one billion dlr Eurobondlaunched last month contributed to September's surplus. REUTER&#3;